<subSubSection pageId="101" pageNumber="101" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="101.[701,1228,213,1066]" pageId="101" pageNumber="101">
COMMENTS: In the original description, Mayr and Gilliard cited the AMNH number of the 
<typeStatus box="[784,886,362,384]" pageId="101" pageNumber="101">holotype</typeStatus>
and mentioned females and young males. Fred Shaw Mayer’s expedition was jointly sponsored by Rothschild and by L.C. Sanford for AMNH and his three specimens of this form were divided between the two collections. The 
<typeStatus box="[1003,1105,510,532]" pageId="101" pageNumber="101">holotype</typeStatus>
had originally been part of the Rothschild Collection share and had come to AMNH with that collection in 1932. The specimens that were part of the original AMNH share were 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[701,893,658,679]" pageId="101" pageNumber="101">AMNH 302945</emphasis>
, immature male, 
<date pageId="101" pageNumber="101" value="1930-07-22">22 July 1930</date>
and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[830,1017,688,709]" pageId="101" pageNumber="101">AMNH 302946</emphasis>
, female, 
<date pageId="101" pageNumber="101" value="1930-07-28">28 July 1930</date>
, Shaw Mayer numbers 212 and 252 respectively; they are both 
<typeStatus box="[1069,1182,748,769]" pageId="101" pageNumber="101">paratypes</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[701,862,776,799]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="101">megarhynchus</emphasis>
as is a single specimen collected by Georg Stein, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1026,1220,806,827]" pageId="101" pageNumber="101">AMNH 302367</emphasis>
, female, Mount Kunupi, Weyland Mountains, 
<date box="[775,960,866,888]" pageId="101" pageNumber="101" value="1931-10-04">4 October 1931</date>
, Stein no. 2934. Shaw Mayer’s collection was reported on by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild" box="[701,913,925,947]" firstAuthor="Rothschild" pageId="101" pageNumber="101" pagination="250 - 276" refId="ref135020" refString="Rothschild, W. 1931. On a collection of birds made by Mr. F. Shaw Mayer in the Weyland Mountans, Dutch New Guinea, in 1930. Novitates Zoologicae 36: 250 - 276." type="journal article" year="1931">Rothschild (1931)</bibRefCitation>
and Stein’s by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hartert" pageId="101" pageNumber="101" pagination="165 - 240" refId="ref126298" refString="Hartert, E., K. Paludan, Lord Rothschild, and E. Stresemann. 1936. Die Vogel des Weyland- Gebirges und seines Vorlandes. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologisches Museum in Berlin 21: 165 - 240." type="journal article" year="1936">Hartert et al. (1936)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="101.[701,1228,213,1066]" pageId="101" pageNumber="101">
<bibRefCitation author="Cracraft" box="[731,972,985,1007]" firstAuthor="Cracraft" page="20" pageId="101" pageNumber="101" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref121493" refString="Cracraft, J. 1992. The species of the birds-ofparadise (Paradisaeidae): applying the phylogenetic species concept to a complex pattern of diversification. Cladistics 8: 1 - 43." type="journal article" year="1992">Cracraft (1992: 20)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="101">megarhynchus</emphasis>
with 
<emphasis box="[890,981,1014,1037]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="101">albicans</emphasis>
, and later authors have agreed.
</paragraph>
